CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FDetention was the "only appropriate
OL,8,Fsentence" for three teenage boys who
OL,9,Fwere spared custody over the rape of
OL,10,Ftwo girls, the Court of Appeal has
OL,11,Fbeen told.
OL,13,FTwo boys aged 15, known as X and Y,
OL,14,Fand another aged 14, known as Z, were
OL,15,Fgiven non-custodial sentences in May
OL,16,Ffor a combined 10 counts of rape and
OL,17,Fseven indecent image offences related
OL,18,Fto two victims, who were separately
OL,19,Fattacked in Fordingbridge, Hampshire,
OL,20,Fin November 2024 and January 2025.
OL,26,@oD@SOUpD@IO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe two older boys were involved in
OL,8,Fboth attacks, while the 14-year-old
OL,9,Fencouraged the rape of the second
OL,10,Fvictim.
OL,12,FSentencing them at Southampton Crown
OL,13,FCourt, Judge Nicholas Rowland said the
OL,14,Foffences of the two 15-year-olds
OL,15,F"crossed the custody threshold", but
OL,16,Fhe should "avoid criminalising these
OL,17,Fchildren unnecessarily" and added that
OL,18,Fdetention was a "last resort".
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@_O]xD@KOUyD@WO]zD@QOUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe sentences were referred to the
OL,8,FCourt of Appeal as "unduly lenient" by
OL,9,FAttorney General Lord Hermer days
OL,10,Flater, following public outcry, with
OL,11,Fbarristers telling a hearing on
OL,12,FWednesday that parts of Judge
OL,13,FRowland's approach to sentencing were
OL,14,F"fundamentally flawed".
OL,16,FThe boys, who have not attended the
OL,17,Fhearing in London, are opposing the
OL,18,Fbids to have their sentences increased.
OL,26,@pD@TOUpD@cO]vD@AOUvD@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FTom Little KC, for the Attorney
OL,8,FGeneral, said: "We accept... that the
OL,9,Fjudge did try to apply the relevant
OL,10,Fprinciples, but our submission is he
OL,11,Fmisapplied them along the way, the
OL,12,Fcumulative effect of which was to lead
OL,13,Fto unduly lenient sentences."
OL,26,@pD@POUuD@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FHe continued: "It is difficult to
OL,8,Funderstand how the judge could
OL,9,Fproperly have come to the conclusion
OL,10,Fthat he did, given the sheer number of
OL,11,Frape offences, which the judge does
OL,12,Fnot properly address in any way in...
OL,13,Fhis sentencing remarks, the underlying
OL,14,Fseriousness of the offending and the
OL,15,Fharm sustained."
OL,17,FX was given a three-year youth
OL,18,Frehabilitation order (YRO) with 180
OL,19,Fdays of intensive supervision and
OL,20,Fsurveillance for raping and taking
OL,21,Findecent images of both victims.
OL,26,@oD@OOUwD@PO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FY received the same sentence for three
OL,8,Fcharges of rape against each of the
OL,9,Ftwo victims and four counts of taking
OL,10,Findecent images by filming the
OL,11,Fincidents.
OL,13,FZ was given an 18-month YRO for two
OL,14,Fcharges of rape related to the latter
OL,15,Fvictim after encouraging the second
OL,16,Fdefendant, and for an offence of
OL,17,Findecent images.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FJudge Rowland said at sentencing that
OL,8,Falthough X and Y were assessed by
OL,9,FYouth Justice Services as "medium
OL,10,Frisk" of reoffending but "high risk of
OL,11,Fserious harm" to young females, he had
OL,12,Fto consider their backgrounds.
OL,14,FHe said X had been diagnosed with ADHD
OL,15,Fand "long-standing anxiety" while Y
OL,16,Fhad an IQ in the bottom 1%, had ADHD
OL,17,Fwith "extreme neurodevelopmental
OL,18,Fimpairment" and presented "more like
OL,19,Fan eight-year-old".
OL,26,@qD@[OUrD@EO]rD@ZOUsD@MO]wD@EOUwD@[O]yD@
OL,26,AFOUzD@KO]zD@[OU{D@RO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Little acknowledged in court that Z
OL,8,Fwas "plainly in a different position"
OL,9,Ffrom X and Y due to his younger age
OL,10,Fand only being involved with one of
OL,11,Fthe rapes, but that his offending was
OL,12,F"sustained".
OL,14,FBut in written submissions, he
OL,15,Fcontinued: "In summary it is submitted
OL,16,Fthat the extent and nature of the
OL,17,Foffending was so serious such that the
OL,18,Fonly appropriate sentence for X, Y and
OL,19,FZ was detention.
OL,26,@pD@EOUpD@eO]tD@AOUtD@KO]wD@LOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"Had the judge properly assessed the
OL,8,Fseriousness of the offences, he could
OL,9,Fonly reasonably have concluded that
OL,10,Flengthy sentences of detention were
OL,11,Frequired for both X and Y and that a
OL,12,Fsentence of detention was required for
OL,13,FZ."
OL,15,FThe barrister also said that the
OL,16,Frestraining order imposed on the three
OL,17,Fboys, preventing them from contacting
OL,18,Feither victim for 10 years, should
OL,19,Fhave been indefinite, adding that this
OL,20,Fhad caused the victims "very
OL,21,Fsignificant concern".
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@CO]|D@XOU}D@TO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FClare Wade KC, for X, said that Judge
OL,8,FRowland "approached the sentencing
OL,9,Fexercise correctly".
OL,11,FShe said: "His approach was
OL,12,Findividualistic, as it should have
OL,13,Fbeen.
OL,15,F"The sentences imposed broadly provide
OL,16,Fthe best opportunity for the child
OL,17,Foffenders to learn and develop and
OL,18,Fprovide the most effective way of
OL,19,Fprotecting women and girls in future
OL,20,Fby preventing future offending."
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@SO]sD@KOUwD@AOU|D@`O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,382,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1782910144
OL,3,CDetention 'only appropriate sentence'
OL,4,Cfor teenage rapists, Court of Appeal
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FIn a statement ahead of the hearing,
OL,8,Fone of the victims said the attack on
OL,9,Fher "has left me harmed so severely
OL,10,Fthat I do not think I will ever be the
OL,11,Fsame" and that the trial of her
OL,12,Fattackers "broke something inside me".
OL,14,FShe said: "I feel like I am carrying
OL,15,Fwhat happened every day. I wake up
OL,16,Fwith it, I go to school with it, I try
OL,17,Fto sit exams with it, and I go to
OL,18,Fsleep with it. It is always there. I
OL,19,Fcannot just switch it off. I cannot
OL,20,Fjust move on."
OL,26,@qD@EOUsD@EO]tD@KOUtD@eO]vD@KOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
